FBIS4-10166 "drlat068_j_94005" FBIS-LAT-94-068 Daily Report 7 Apr 1994 Panama Peru Resumes Diplomatic Relations Peru Resumes Diplomatic Relations PA0804010994 Panama City Circuito RPC Television in Spanish 2300 GMT 7 Apr 94 PA0804010994 Panama City Circuito RPC Television Spanish BFN [From the "RPC Television News" newscast] [Text] The Governments of Panama and Peru mutually agreed to resume diplomatic relations, according to a Panamanian Foreign Ministry communique. The communique states that the decision was made following Foreign Minister Jose Mulino's visit to Peru. Both nations made the decision following a discussion during Mulino's visit of the historical ties uniting them, their traditional ties of friendship, and the noble goal of Latin American integration.
